cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.DM, cs.CC 

This paper deals with machine learning and optimization techniques, specifically structured output SVM and multi-label problems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses supermodular functions, which are commonly studied in the field of combinatorial optimization, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) likely categories as well. The use of convex surrogates and extensions also suggests a connection to optimization and convex analysis, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible category. Finally, the paper discusses families of functions and their relationships, which could fall under the category of cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
